          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
        Russia-Ukraine swap overshadowed
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/largest-pow-exchange-ukrainian-civilians-russia-war.jpg" alt="The prisoner exchange was the latest of scores of swaps since the war began but also the biggest involving Ukrainian civilians" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>
          The prisoner exchange was the latest of scores of swaps since the war began but also the biggest involving Ukrainian civilians. Credits: Ukrainian Presidential Press Service via Reuters</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
    Russia and Ukraine completed a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-26-may-25-spotlight-h1-1-historic-prisoner-exchange" target="_blank">historic prisoner exchange</a>, swapping 303 soldiers from each side. This was the last phase of a three-part swap involving 1,000 detainees. This rare cooperation followed peace talks in Istanbul. Zelenskyy confirmed the return of prisoners, including members of the Armed Forces, National Guard, and other military services.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      But a massive Russian missile and drone attack killed at least 12 people, including three children, and injured dozens. The attack hit over 30 Ukrainian cities and villages, including its capital, Kyiv. The day was somber as the city observed Kyiv Day, a national holiday commemorating its founding in the 5th century. There was no immediate comment from Moscow on the strikes.</p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Russia used 69 missiles of various types and 298 drones, including Iranian-designed Shahed drones, marking the largest single aerial attack of the more than three-year-long war. Zelenskyy condemned the attack and urged Western partners to ramp up sanctions. Washington condemned the Russian attacks, calling them ‚Äúa clear violation‚Äù of the Geneva Protocols.</p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Meanwhile, Russia‚Äôs Defense Ministry said its air defenses shot down 110 Ukrainian drones overnight.</p>
