        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-top:4px;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáªüá™ Venezuela - Election results.</strong> Venezuela‚Äôs ruling Socialist Party, led by Nicol√°s Maduro, clinched a sweeping victory. After last year's disputed vote, the opposition boycotted the election and accused the ruling party of fraud. More than 70 people were arrested on suspicion of planning to "sabotage" the election. The election validates Maduro‚Äôs grip on power in Venezuela (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-26-may-25-worldwide-8-election-boycott" target="_blank">election boycott</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáµüá∏ Palestine - Hamas dead in a tunnel.</strong>   Israeli airstrikes in Gaza reportedly killed Mohammed Sinwar, Hamas‚Äôs leader and brother of Yahya Sinwar, who was killed in 2024. His body was found in a tunnel in Khan Younis alongside aides. The strikes, part of Israel‚Äôs expanded offensive, also targeted hospitals (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-26-may-25-worldwide-9-more-about-his-death" target="_blank">more about his death</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá™üá∏ Spain- Holds conference.</strong> Spain hosted over 20 European and Arab nations in Madrid to urge Israel to halt its Gaza offensive and allow humanitarian aid. Spanish FM Jos√© Manuel Albares calls the war ‚Äúinhumane‚Äù and wants recognition of Palestine and sanctions on Israel. The meeting preceded a UN summit on the two-state solution, co-hosted by France and Saudi Arabia (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-26-may-25-worldwide-10-spain-takes-the-reins" target="_blank">Spain takes the reins</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá±üáß Lebanon - Deals with Palestinians.</strong> 
           Lebanon and the Palestinian Authority have agreed to dismantle Palestinian factions in refugee camps, aiming to end the decades-long armed presence in the country. President Mahmoud Abbas and Lebanese leaders emphasized state control over all weapons, though Abbas lacks authority over groups like Hamas (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-26-may-25-worldwide-11-more-about-palestinians-in-lebanon" target="_blank">more about Palestinians in Lebanon</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáπüá∑ Turkey - FM visits Russia.</strong> 
            FM Hakan Fidan will visit Russia this week to discuss the Ukraine conflict. Fidan will emphasize Turkey‚Äôs commitment to a fair peace. He will also address regional issues, including Syria, Gaza, and the South Caucasus, further establishing Turkey‚Äôs role as a diplomatic mediator (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-26-may-25-worldwide-12-turkish-russian-connection" target="_blank">Turkish-Russian connection</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáµüá∞ Pakistan - PM visits Turkey.</strong> 
            Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdoƒüan met Pakistani PM Shehbaz Sharif to strengthen ties in defense, energy, and intelligence cooperation following the recent India-Pakistan conflict. Erdoƒüan voiced support for Pakistan and denied supplying weapons during the clash (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-26-may-25-worldwide-13-turkish-pakistani-connection" target="_blank">Turkish-Pakistani connection</a>).
